'''[[Dust devil]]s''' can be assigned as a slayer task by various medium and high-levelled [[Slayer Master]]s upon reaching 65 [[Slayer]] and 70 combat. In order to obtain these as a Slayer task, the player must have started [[Desert Treasure I]].

Dust devils are an incredibly popular task amongst most slayers, as they have a superior, the [[choke devil]], and are often found in [[multicombat area]]s which allows for chinning and burst/barraging. They have relatively decent drops which usually covers the cost of supplies.

Unlike most monsters, dust devils attack with [[ranged melee]]; their attacks are considered melee, but they roll on the player's ranged defence rather than melee. They have low defence but are surprisingly accurate for their level.

Players have three options to choose from when slaying dust devils:

*[[Catacombs of Kourend]] - this is the most easily accessible location. Dust devils here have access to the Catacombs of Kourend drop table.
*[[Smoke Dungeon]] - a more remote, quiet location. A multicombat area can be found to the west for on-task purposes.
*[[Wilderness Slayer Cave]] - a somewhat busy location, can only be killed on-task. This location is in level 25-28 [[Wilderness]], so '''do not bring items you are unwilling to lose.''' A large amount of costs can be lowered via [[Blighted ancient ice sack]]s and the dust devils here have access to the Wilderness Slayer Cave drop table.

Unless killing them as part of [[Konar quo Maten]] or [[Krystilia]]'s Slayer tasks, the Catacombs of Kourend are highly recommended for their ease of accessibility.
