This is the best-in-slot available equipment for maging dust devils. See the table below for an overview of equipment alternatives in case this setup is not accessible or too expensive.

===Notes===
*The [[occult necklace]] (+5%), [[tormented bracelet]] (+5%), [[imbued god capes]] (+2%), and [[virtus robes]] (+2% each) or [[ancestral robes]] (+3% each) increase the maximum hit of the player's Magic spells. However, the tormented bracelet is generally inefficient to use as the [[bracelet of slaughter]] will increase the task's length and maximise overall Slayer experience rates.
*It is recommended to use a staff or wand that can autocast [[Ancient Magicks]]. [[Kodai wand]] provides +15% magic damage bonus as well as infinite water runes and a chance to save runes, making it the most effective.
*A [[goading potion]], darts, knives, or a blowpipe may be used to lure. The special attack of the [[Dinh's bulwark]] in conjunction with a [[Lightbearer]] may also be used to lure, however it may cause stamina issues due to its weight for players with lower agility levels.
*A [[Hunters' crossbow]] or [[Hunters' sunlight crossbow]] is also an effective luring weapon, having the same speed as shortbows and 1 more tile of range. It is also 1-handed, so magic off-hands aren't unequipped. [[Kebbit bolts]] and [[sunlight antler bolts]] are much more expensive than the cheapest arrows and darts, however [[Long kebbit bolts]] are currently very cheap.
*A [[venator bow]] can also be effectively used.

